Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.98,0:00:04.31,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,We made it to Whitesails!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.31,0:00:06.15,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Haven't been here in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.57,0:00:07.49,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Will?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.72,0:00:11.14,Main,Will,0,0,0,,It's amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.87,0:00:24.16,Show_Title,Title,0,0,0,,{\fad(1075,0)\blur2\pos(320,290)}The Faraway Paladin
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.97,0:01:47.60,Main,Will,0,0,0,,There's no entry inspection or toll?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.60,0:01:48.92,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.92,0:01:52.41,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,It's the policy of His Excellency \NEthel, the city's ruler.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.41,0:01:55.95,Main - Top,Tonio,0,0,0,,Goods enter this city by boat \Nin tremendous amounts,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.05,0:02:00.30,Episode_Title,Title,0,0,0,,{\fad(575,0)\pos(498,280)}Episode 9\N{\fs24}Whitesails
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.95,0:02:00.30,Main - Top,Tonio,0,0,0,,and then they're distributed throughout \NSouthmark by land and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.30,0:02:04.28,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Wouldn't that mean a massive amount \Nof goods pass through here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.28,0:02:06.84,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,Yes, and if all of them \Nare checked at the gate,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.84,0:02:09.81,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,it would be a hotbed for smuggling \Nof both goods and people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.81,0:02:11.06,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.06,0:02:13.60,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,So Ethel imposed docking fees \Nfor ships and rental fees
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.60,0:02:17.36,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,for companies setting up shop here \Nto make money for the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.36,0:02:21.70,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,keeping the movement of people and \Ngoods as unrestricted as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.70,0:02:22.87,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.30,0:02:26.94,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,It seems like the economy \Nis their top priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.94,0:02:29.78,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,It's a very advanced city, \Nwith a real sense of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.37,0:02:33.10,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Quit talking about all that boring stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.10,0:02:35.52,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,It's Will's first time here! \NLet's have fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.52,0:02:37.01,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,C'mon, this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.43,0:02:42.90,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Will, this is the city's biggest market.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.90,0:02:44.88,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Wow... People...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.88,0:02:46.27,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Why is that surprising?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.27,0:02:47.89,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Oh, over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.89,0:02:51.31,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Look! These accessories \Nare in style right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.31,0:02:52.38,Main,Will,0,0,0,,In style?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.38,0:02:53.82,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.82,0:02:55.89,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,There are things "in style" here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.24,0:02:55.89,Main - Top,Menel,0,0,0,,Is this stone worth a lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.89,0:02:58.11,Main - Top,Bee,0,0,0,,Aw, jeez, Menel...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.89,0:02:59.93,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,That means these people can \Nafford to think about fashion!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.22,0:03:04.45,Main,Will,0,0,0,,It's just one shock after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.60,0:03:06.70,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.70,0:03:08.17,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,A street light.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.17,0:03:09.06,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Street light?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.06,0:03:10.55,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,You don't know what those are?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.55,0:03:12.78,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Gosh, Will, you're so behind the times!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.78,0:03:15.32,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Apprentices from the Academy of Sages
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.32,0:03:17.84,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,come by in the evenings, lighting up posts
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.84,0:03:21.09,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,that have Words of Light engraved on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.09,0:03:23.73,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,So the people here have \Nlight even at night!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.73,0:03:26.23,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,It serves as training for \Napprentice sorcerers,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.23,0:03:29.39,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,and they earn a little pocket money, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.39,0:03:34.14,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,That over there is also a large source \Nof income for apprentice sorcerers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.14,0:03:35.24,Main,Will,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.06,0:03:38.96,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Even you must know what that is!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.35,0:03:42.12,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,It's the public bathhouse, Balnea!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.12,0:03:43.47,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Balnea?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.18,0:03:46.08,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.08,0:03:49.03,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,A public bathhouse?! They have baths?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.79,0:03:53.71,Main,Will,0,0,0,,The water's so clean, \Nyou can see through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.71,0:03:57.13,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,Yes, that's an effect of the \NWords of Purification.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.13,0:04:01.51,Words,Text,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Heat
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.47,0:04:00.42,Main - Top,Tonio,0,0,0,,Instead of the massive amounts of fuel \Nit would take to heat the baths,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.42,0:04:02.67,Main - Top,Tonio,0,0,0,,they use Words of Heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.67,0:04:04.00,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.00,0:04:08.43,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,So it's less like a bath and more \Nlike a sauna and a cold water pool,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.43,0:04:09.89,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,but it's still amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.89,0:04:15.95,Main,Will,0,0,0,,The breeze feels so nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.28,0:04:20.55,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,I used Words of Purification to \Nkeep up good hygiene on the road,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.55,0:04:23.18,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,but it's great to have actual baths.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.78,0:04:26.71,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Boy, it feels good to have \Na bath after so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.71,0:04:27.87,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,That's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.87,0:04:30.68,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,I just hope things don't get all messy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.13,0:04:32.66,Main,Will,0,0,0,,What are we doing next?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.60,0:04:35.34,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Next is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.69,0:04:40.33,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Man, I'm always so hungry after a bath!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.71,0:04:44.51,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,You two must've been starving, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.51,0:04:46.29,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,The food is quite good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.29,0:04:47.44,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.44,0:04:50.64,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,I think it could've been a \Nlittle juicier, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.64,0:04:53.16,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,It's absorbed the flavor \Nof the fish so well,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.16,0:04:54.65,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,and the saltiness is just right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.90,0:04:57.77,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,I haven't eaten anything like \Nthis since I left the temple!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.77,0:05:00.67,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,It tastes like... civilization!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.87,0:05:04.29,Main,Will,0,0,0,,It's all so good,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.29,0:05:07.09,Main,Will,0,0,0,,we lost track of the conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.29,0:05:11.61,Main,Will,0,0,0,,This is good, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.61,0:05:13.47,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Can I get a refill on this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.47,0:05:14.70,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.70,0:05:16.16,Main,Server,0,0,0,,Coming right up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.16,0:05:19.18,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,When we're finished eating, \Nwe'll head to the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.18,0:05:22.68,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,Since you're a priest, Will, \Nyou need to pay your respects, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.68,0:05:24.87,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Oh... Yes, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.57,0:05:28.54,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.89,0:05:30.63,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,They spent a lot of money on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.63,0:05:32.71,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Jeez, Menel...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.71,0:05:34.77,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I'll be back as soon as I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.77,0:05:36.38,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Please wait here for just a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.23,0:05:42.10,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,Are temples in cities always this big?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.10,0:05:45.07,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,They all look like works of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.07,0:05:47.35,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,It feels more like a tourist destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.13,0:05:49.81,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Um, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.81,0:05:51.64,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,Yes, how can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.64,0:05:54.58,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Is there a high-ranking priest here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.58,0:05:57.46,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I've received divine protection \Nand become a priest,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.46,0:05:59.02,Main,Will,0,0,0,,so I wanted to pay my respects.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.02,0:06:03.01,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,Ah... Pardon my asking, \Nbut which deity do you serve?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.01,0:06:05.60,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Gracefeel, the goddess of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.03,0:06:09.81,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,Oh... The goddess of light? \NThat is a problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.81,0:06:11.01,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.01,0:06:13.23,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,Priests of the goddess of \Nlight are quite uncommon,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.23,0:06:16.73,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,so our rules compel me to use \Nthe Prayer of Faith Detection.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.73,0:06:18.47,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Okay, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.82,0:06:20.58,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,I guess that makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.58,0:06:23.08,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,It's inevitable that people \Nwould be skeptical
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.08,0:06:24.76,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,of a priest to a minor god.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.76,0:06:27.53,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,I could be a priest to an \Nevil god in disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.86,0:06:31.31,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,The thing is... all those \Nwith the divine protection
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.31,0:06:34.94,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,that qualifies them to determine \Nanother's faith are out right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.94,0:06:36.47,Main,Will,0,0,0,,They're all out?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.47,0:06:41.37,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,Yes. Attacks by demon beasts have been \Non the rise everywhere recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.37,0:06:44.96,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,All but the vice bishop are \Nextremely busy at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.96,0:06:46.03,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,Vice...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.03,0:06:48.75,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,What are you doing in the \Nmiddle of the aisle?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.75,0:06:50.29,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,Bishop Bagley!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.55,0:06:52.76,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,I asked you what you're doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.76,0:06:54.79,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,Uh, well... j-just...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.79,0:06:56.57,Main,Will,0,0,0,,It's an honor to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.57,0:06:59.18,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I am William G. Maryblood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.53,0:07:03.04,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I have earned the divine protection \Nof Gracefeel, goddess of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.04,0:07:06.43,Main,Will,0,0,0,,and have come to the temple of \NWhitesails to pay my respects.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.77,0:07:08.73,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.28,0:07:12.70,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,Bart Bagley. I am in charge of this temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.70,0:07:14.48,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,Gracefeel...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.48,0:07:17.93,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,The goddess of light, a deity \Nwho has been all but lost?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.93,0:07:21.40,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,And how do I know that you are not some \Nsuspicious individual using her name
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.40,0:07:23.57,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,for some insidious plot?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.57,0:07:25.88,Main,Will,0,0,0,,You have every right to be suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.88,0:07:28.50,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Is there anything I can \Nbless to prove myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.50,0:07:32.77,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,Hah! You novices are so quick to \Nrely on your divine protection!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.22,0:07:38.11,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,Listen to me. Divine protection is \Nnot something to be used lightly,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.11,0:07:40.47,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,nor is it something to use ostentatiously.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.69,0:07:43.11,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,He has a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.11,0:07:46.04,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,Gus said the same thing about using magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.04,0:07:49.50,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,I was using my blessing without concern \Nsince it poses little risk, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.36,0:07:52.31,Main,Will,0,0,0,,You are right, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.31,0:07:55.34,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I truly thank you for reminding \Nme of my lack of exper—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.34,0:07:56.07,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,Hmph!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.07,0:07:59.44,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,What are the teachings of the \Ngoddess of light to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.74,0:08:01.67,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Light can only exist where \Nthere is darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.67,0:08:03.73,Main,Will,0,0,0,,words can only exist \Nwhere there is silence,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.73,0:08:06.46,Main,Will,0,0,0,,and life can only exist \Nwhere there is death.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.47,0:08:12.33,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,You. Put his name in the registry \Nand show him around the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.33,0:08:13.10,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.10,0:08:17.10,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,But we haven't performed the Prayer of Faith \NDetection or the Prayer of Lie Detection...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.10,0:08:17.75,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,Fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.75,0:08:20.22,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,What did I just say, you imbecile?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.51,0:08:24.85,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,I need to make an appearance at \Nthe Weaver's Guild banquet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.85,0:08:28.27,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,Spend your time as you please, \Nbut do not cause any trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.27,0:08:30.61,Main,Bagley,0,0,0,,And do offer some money.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.95,0:08:34.36,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,W-Well, then, right this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.36,0:08:35.44,Main,Will,0,0,0,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.40,0:08:40.91,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,How unpleasant it must have been for \Nyou to have met Bishop Bagley.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.91,0:08:42.90,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,But you handled yourself very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.90,0:08:43.70,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.70,0:08:47.84,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,Well, the head of the temple loses himself \Nin parties and pleasure-seeking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.84,0:08:49.67,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,He's quick to anger and \Ncomplains constantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.67,0:08:52.53,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,Despite all he says, \Nhe never uses his blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.85,0:08:56.34,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,The vice bishop, on the other hand, \Nis a wonderful, virtuous person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.34,0:08:56.92,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.02,0:09:00.68,Main,Deacon,0,0,0,,Oh, dear, I'm sorry! \NDon't tell anyone I said that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.68,0:09:01.66,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.76,0:09:05.68,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Hey, what do you know about \Nthe head of the temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.68,0:09:09.18,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Hmm... I haven't heard many \Ngood things about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.18,0:09:10.72,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Like, they say he's vulgar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.72,0:09:12.90,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,He seems to have some \Nsort of influence behind-the-scenes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.90,0:09:16.08,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,of the city's commercial and \Nindustrial guilds, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.31,0:09:18.52,Main,Will,0,0,0,,So that's how he's seen around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.52,0:09:20.56,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Still, talk about living it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.56,0:09:23.09,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,I can't believe he let us use \Nthe temple's guest room!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.09,0:09:24.70,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Two of them, even!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.70,0:09:27.08,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,Anyway, what shall we do next?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.08,0:09:30.25,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,We could take in the sights, \Nor visit some guilds...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.25,0:09:33.19,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Oh, if we do that, I'd recommend the...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.19,0:09:35.42,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Hang on. Something's going on outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.42,0:09:37.85,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,That's not the bell that gives the time. \NThey're hammering it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.85,0:09:39.16,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Is there a fire or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.16,0:09:41.42,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,It's an emergency alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.76,0:09:44.11,Main,Townie,0,0,0,,It's a wyvern! Everybody run!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.11,0:09:45.00,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.43,0:10:03.57,Main,KnightA,0,0,0,,Move! Be ready for anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.57,0:10:06.28,Main,ManA,0,0,0,,Someone come help us! \NA person's pinned under rubble!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.28,0:10:07.92,Main,InjuredB,0,0,0,,Ow, ow, ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.92,0:10:09.35,Main,ManB,0,0,0,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.30,0:10:10.08,Main - Top,Priest,0,0,0,,Don't push! Please stop pushing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.08,0:10:11.95,Main,WomanA,0,0,0,,Has anyone seen my child?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.95,0:10:13.25,Main,Old,0,0,0,,Oh, gods...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.56,0:10:23.72,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Will, wait! Will!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.20,0:10:31.93,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,Why is a wyvern here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.93,0:10:34.95,Main,KnightB,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.36,0:10:40.54,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,He said all the high-ranking \Nclergy are out right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.15,0:10:48.53,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,Their civilization... Their city...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.95,0:10:51.23,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,Everything the three of them protected...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.23,0:10:53.54,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,The place where people can live freely...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.56,0:10:57.38,Main - Top,Will,0,0,0,,Verba!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.67,0:10:57.17,Words,Text,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Words
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.38,0:10:58.21,Main - Top,Will,0,0,0,,Volanto!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.42,0:10:57.92,Words,Text,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Fly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.17,0:10:58.92,Words,Text,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Thunder
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.21,0:10:59.40,Main - Top,Will,0,0,0,,Tonitrus!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.10,0:11:02.28,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,It missed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.59,0:11:06.59,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,But those are the longest-ranged \NWords I can use!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.84,0:11:09.59,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,Then I'll just have to keep \Nfiring until I hit it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.59,0:11:11.66,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,You idiot! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.66,0:11:14.92,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Why are you shooting off high magic \Nlike that in a blind fury?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.92,0:11:16.07,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,You'll get yourself killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.07,0:11:16.72,Main,Will,0,0,0,,But—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.72,0:11:17.56,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,No buts!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.56,0:11:21.11,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,You're fighting a wyvern! \NI'm telling you to be more efficient!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.11,0:11:23.69,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,You've got smarts, so use 'em, moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.69,0:11:25.34,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Don't just rush in!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.70,0:11:31.03,Flashback,Gus,0,0,0,,You'll start by learning how to use \Nminor magic skillfully and accurately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.62,0:11:33.77,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.77,0:11:34.79,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.16,0:11:39.70,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,Think. What can I do about this \Nwyvern using what I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.31,0:11:43.44,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Menel, would you help me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.44,0:11:45.46,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I need you and your fairies.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.46,0:11:46.19,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.90,0:11:48.40,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Bee, Tonio!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.40,0:11:52.61,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Work with the people nearby to get everyone \Nclear of the temple's front garden!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.61,0:11:54.76,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I'm going to bring the wyvern down there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.76,0:11:55.69,Main,Priest,0,0,0,,Your Excellency!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.69,0:11:57.91,Main,Priest,0,0,0,,You must take shelter below, quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.91,0:11:59.44,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,How could this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.44,0:12:02.79,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Dozens of people... hundreds of \Npeople... are going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.36,0:12:05.94,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Now, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.94,0:12:09.00,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Sylphs, Sylphs, maidens of wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.00,0:12:11.17,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Your steps are the wind's steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.17,0:12:13.02,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Your song is the wind's song.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.45,0:12:16.93,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Sing in chorus, sing in rounds, \Ncheer and applaud.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.32,0:12:21.64,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Your harmony shall spread the Words \Nof Origin in the ten directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.88,0:12:22.42,Words,Text,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Words
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.89,0:12:22.78,Main - Top,Will,0,0,0,,Verba.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.76,0:12:23.38,Words,Text,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Fly
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.78,0:12:23.77,Main - Top,Will,0,0,0,,Volanto.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.77,0:12:24.83,Main - Top,Will,0,0,0,,Conciliat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.88,0:12:24.64,Words,Text,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Unite
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.76,0:12:25.51,Words,Text,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Follow
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.83,0:12:25.63,Main - Top,Will,0,0,0,,Sequitur.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.89,0:12:26.64,Words,Text,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Thunder
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.89,0:12:26.87,Main - Top,Will,0,0,0,,Tonitrus...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.87,0:12:27.77,Main - Top,Will,0,0,0,,Araneum!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.89,0:12:27.64,Words,Text,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Spiderweb
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.82,0:12:40.14,Main,KnightC,0,0,0,,Is that... magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.14,0:12:43.26,Main,KnightD,0,0,0,,There's a fairy user, too? \NBoy, are we lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.26,0:12:45.52,Main,KnightC,0,0,0,,We've got this! We can do it! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.29,0:12:52.38,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,I'm probably not hurting it that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.60,0:12:55.65,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,But that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.06,0:12:58.62,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,So long as the wyvern identifies \Nus as its enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.62,0:13:01.55,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,Almost all beasts of this \Ntype are highly aggressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.55,0:13:03.65,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,Even in situations where \Nthey could get away,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.65,0:13:05.53,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,they'll choose to take the offensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.84,0:13:06.75,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Here it comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.75,0:13:07.39,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.23,0:13:14.47,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,The rest depends on how close \Nmy skills have come to theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.91,0:13:18.44,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,Goddess, I now fight for \Nthe sake of my oath.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.44,0:13:21.76,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,To banish evil and save the suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.76,0:13:23.85,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,Pray! Pray!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.85,0:13:25.86,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,Be as unbreakable as adamantine!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.86,0:13:28.46,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,For eternity... For all eternity...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.16,0:13:31.20,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,Reject all that is evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.20,0:13:33.78,Main,Will,0,0,0,,On the flame of Gracefeel!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.66,0:13:45.56,Main,Townie,0,0,0,,What the heck is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.31,0:13:54.82,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Sylphs! Beautiful maidens of \Nwind, dancers in the gale!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.82,0:13:57.81,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Show those foolish enough to fancy themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.81,0:14:00.10,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,better dancers the bitter taste of earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.28,0:14:06.31,Main - Top,Will,0,0,0,,Ligatur!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.40,0:14:06.15,Words,Text,0,0,0,,Be Tied
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.28,0:14:07.03,Words,Text,0,0,0,,Knot
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.31,0:14:07.03,Main - Top,Will,0,0,0,,Nodus!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.03,0:14:08.47,Main - Top,Will,0,0,0,,Obligatio!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.15,0:14:08.24,Words,Text,0,0,0,,Binding
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.00,0:14:12.13,Main,KnightE,0,0,0,,It's bound!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.13,0:14:15.30,Main,KnightD,0,0,0,,No, it's trying to tear them off! \NDamn, it's strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.90,0:14:17.21,Main - Top,Will,0,0,0,,Acceleratio!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.00,0:14:17.08,Words,Text,0,0,0,,Accelerate
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.79,0:14:22.00,Main,Townfolk,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.29,0:14:26.59,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.91,0:14:28.47,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,That didn't finish it off?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.42,0:14:31.38,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Run! It's gonna use its breath!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.70,0:14:33.52,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,There are still people back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.52,0:14:35.89,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,What do I do? What can I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.44,0:14:39.40,Flashback,Blood,0,0,0,,Get 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.00,0:14:41.22,Main - Top,Will,0,0,0,,Acceleratio!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.02,0:14:41.11,Words,Text,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Accelerate
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.61,0:14:46.44,Flashback_Italics,Blood,0,0,0,,If you don't know, use your muscles!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.44,0:14:48.99,Flashback_Italics,Blood,0,0,0,,Be violent! Get 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.74,0:14:57.87,Main,Priest,0,0,0,,A n-neck throw?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.88,0:15:03.53,Main,Will,0,0,0,,You're not getting away!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.62,0:15:11.56,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Your fangs and claws will harm no one!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.78,0:15:32.15,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,Well done! Excellent work!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.15,0:15:38.16,Main,Tonio,0,0,0,,I give thanks to all the gods for allowing \Nme to serve a hero such as you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.16,0:15:42.79,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,It's the birth of a new Wyvern Killer! \NA brand new hero!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.79,0:15:45.42,Main,Bee,0,0,0,,Sing his praises with your applause!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.62,0:15:50.63,Main,People,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.05,0:15:51.96,Main,People,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.55,0:15:53.96,Main,People,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.69,0:15:59.63,Main,KnightD,0,0,0,,I guess we were too late, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.22,0:16:02.77,Main,KnightC,0,0,0,,Still, I had no idea so many magic users
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.77,0:16:05.98,Main,KnightC,0,0,0,,and a warrior strong enough to \Nkill a wyvern were staying here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.98,0:16:08.03,Main,KnightC,0,0,0,,It is truly divine providence!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.34,0:16:18.05,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,I guess anything goes with you, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.05,0:16:19.21,Main,Will,0,0,0,,You're surprised?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.21,0:16:21.18,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,I'm used to the way you defy logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.94,0:16:26.31,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Well, I was reminded of \Nhow inexperienced I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.31,0:16:26.80,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.80,0:16:29.00,Main,Will,0,0,0,,It was great for a first attempt,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.00,0:16:31.18,Main,Will,0,0,0,,but I was just lucky to \Nland a surprise attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.18,0:16:34.33,Main,Will,0,0,0,,And what was that black miasma around it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.33,0:16:35.00,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.00,0:16:36.85,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,You brought down a real monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.85,0:16:39.13,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Critique yourself all you want, \Nbut at least be a little bit happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.13,0:16:41.43,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,It's hard for me to be happy if you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.86,0:16:42.69,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.35,0:16:44.97,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,When he puts it that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.97,0:16:46.84,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,There's a lot I could've done better,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.84,0:16:49.52,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,but now I'm a Wyvern Killer \Nlike the three of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.91,0:16:51.97,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,That makes me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.19,0:16:53.88,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Yeah... Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.88,0:16:56.94,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Thanks, Menel! I owe it all to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.94,0:16:58.79,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Yeah. We did it, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.28,0:17:04.17,Main,Menel,0,0,0,,Also, you know damn well it was \Nnearly all your doing, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.87,0:17:07.37,Main,Priest,0,0,0,,Wyvern Killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.19,0:17:10.48,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Yes, that's me! What can I do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.48,0:17:12.38,Main,Priest,0,0,0,,Please come with me, quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.38,0:17:13.79,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.79,0:17:17.60,Main,Priest,0,0,0,,The crown prince wishes to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.72,0:17:22.24,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Welcome to my mansion, hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.59,0:17:27.73,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,So this is the crown prince of the \NFertile Kingdom, the lord of Whitesails,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.73,0:17:29.80,Italics,Will,0,0,0,,and the ruler of Southmark...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.40,0:17:35.73,Main,Will,0,0,0,,It is a greater honor than I deserve \Nto stand in Your Highness's presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.73,0:17:38.63,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I have come here per your request.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.63,0:17:41.02,Main,Will,0,0,0,,My name is William G. Maryblood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.02,0:17:44.29,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Oh? You are well-versed \Nin the old etiquette.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.29,0:17:46.37,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,I assume you are of high birth?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.37,0:17:48.18,Main,Will,0,0,0,,No, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.18,0:17:51.33,Main,Will,0,0,0,,If Your Highness could please refrain \Nfrom asking about my origins...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.37,0:17:55.47,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,You have your circumstances, then. \NI understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.66,0:17:59.40,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Please, have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.40,0:18:00.29,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.28,0:18:18.12,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,William, there are four or five \Nin your group, are there not?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.12,0:18:19.66,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Yes, four of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.66,0:18:23.99,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Which makes you a magic user, a priest, \Na fairy user, and a warrior?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.99,0:18:24.66,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.24,0:18:31.06,Main,Will,0,0,0,,A traveling priest, hunter, \Nmerchant, and bard, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.01,0:18:35.78,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,One who shot lightning at the wyvern, \None who made a wall of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.78,0:18:39.39,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,one who controlled air currents, \Nand one who broke its neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.39,0:18:40.64,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,That makes four, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.64,0:18:44.55,Main,Will,0,0,0,,If that makes four people, \Nit is indeed correct we are two of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.25,0:18:46.54,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.54,0:18:48.82,Main,Will,0,0,0,,My friend there, Meneldor, \Ncalled the fairies,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.82,0:18:51.56,Main,Will,0,0,0,,spread Words, \Nand manipulated the air currents
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.56,0:18:54.93,Main,Will,0,0,0,,to bring the wyvern down to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.93,0:18:58.05,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,So he is the fairy user, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.05,0:18:59.03,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,And the rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.03,0:19:00.66,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.03,0:19:06.79,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but would you mind \Ntelling me what you did?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.60,0:19:12.87,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I used brute force to break its neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.87,0:19:15.79,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,You kill a wyvern and feel no pride?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.79,0:19:18.38,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,You really are a warrior \Nof unparalleled bravery.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.38,0:19:19.45,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.33,0:19:23.42,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Does anything need to be done to fix \Nthe damage that the wyvern caused?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.74,0:19:27.05,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Of course, work has already been \Ndone, and more is yet to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.31,0:19:30.76,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,But there is something more \Nimportant that must be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.99,0:19:35.42,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Yes. Offering my thanks to \Nthe hero, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.42,0:19:36.78,Main,Will,0,0,0,,No, I—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.78,0:19:38.52,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Do not be modest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.52,0:19:41.82,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,I do not want my people to see \Nme as an ungrateful man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.89,0:19:48.51,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,I, Ethelbald, thank you both on behalf \Nof the people of Whitesails.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.15,0:19:53.96,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,You did well to minimize the damage \Ncaused by a wyvern's surprise attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.96,0:19:56.62,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I am unworthy of such praise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.46,0:20:01.55,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,I would like to give you a reward. \NIs there anything you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.90,0:20:08.73,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I traveled here today via \NBeast Woods to the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.09,0:20:11.48,Main,Will,0,0,0,,The villages in that area \Nare currently under threat
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.48,0:20:15.39,Main,Will,0,0,0,,by an army of demons commanding \Nsavage demon beasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.90,0:20:19.22,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Um, if I may ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.48,0:20:21.73,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Would it be possible for Your Highness
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.73,0:20:24.89,Main,Will,0,0,0,,to send soldiers to hunt down the demons?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.89,0:20:26.69,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,It's not impossible,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.69,0:20:28.50,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,but it would be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.50,0:20:30.50,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,You saw that wyvern.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.50,0:20:32.74,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Demon beasts much like it have \Nbeen causing frequent incidents
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.74,0:20:35.33,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,within the parts of \NSouthmark that I govern.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.33,0:20:36.70,Main,Will,0,0,0,,You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.70,0:20:39.29,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Yes. It's that toxic miasma.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.73,0:20:42.71,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Any being it touches is corrupted \Nby the poison and turns savage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.23,0:20:45.80,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Are you certain you are \Nwell yourself, William?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.13,0:20:48.38,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I am naturally resistant to poisons.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.38,0:20:50.02,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,That is good to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.50,0:20:52.31,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Under the previous king's policies,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.31,0:20:54.39,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,we expanded our domain too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.39,0:20:59.27,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,We cannot even sufficiently protect \Nthe villages we directly govern.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.58,0:21:01.68,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Do you understand my meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.27,0:21:07.15,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Then... would you give me permission
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.15,0:21:09.36,Main,Will,0,0,0,,to hire adventurers and \Nmercenaries with my own money
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.36,0:21:12.03,Main,Will,0,0,0,,and organize an army to \Ndrive out the demons?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.05,0:21:19.08,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,William, do you realize \Nwhat that would mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.08,0:21:23.52,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I understand that I am asking \Na great deal of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.52,0:21:25.67,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Yet you stand by your request?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.02,0:21:26.77,Main,Will,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.29,0:21:28.82,Main,Will,0,0,0,,If I do not,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.82,0:21:32.82,Main,Will,0,0,0,,how many tragedies would we be \Nforced to simply overlook?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.82,0:21:37.68,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,But to save everyone is a task \Nnot even the gods can achieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.56,0:21:44.18,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,Honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.18,0:21:48.54,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,If only you were some nameless man \Nmaking this request of me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.54,0:21:49.94,Main,Will,0,0,0,,You are right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.94,0:21:52.58,Main,Will,0,0,0,,That said, had I not killed the wyvern,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.58,0:21:55.09,Main,Will,0,0,0,,I may never have had the opportunity \Nto speak with Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.09,0:21:56.97,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,That is also true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.30,0:21:58.25,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.07,0:22:03.03,Main,Ethelbald,0,0,0,,I must also consider the \Noption of killing you.
